import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_sum = data.groupby(['origin']).sum().reset_index()
    data_sum = data_sum.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False)
    chart = sns.barplot(x='origin', y='count', data=data_sum)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight counts between different airports?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('Airport')
    plt.ylabel('Flight Count')
    chart.legend(title='Airports', loc='upper right', labels=data_sum['origin'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    average_flights = data['count'].mean()
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='count', bins=30, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(average_flights, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {average_flights:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the average number of flights per airport?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_origin = data.groupby('origin')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    data_destination = data.groupby('destination')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    data_total = pd.concat([data_origin, data_destination], ignore_index=True)
    data_total = data_total.groupby(data_total.columns[0])['count'].sum().reset_index()
    data_total.columns = ['airport', 'count']
    data_total = data_total.sort_values('count', ascending=False)

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='airport', y='count', data=data_total.head(10), palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the most popular airport for flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Airport')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Top 10 Airports', loc='upper right')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['airport'] = data['origin'].append(data['destination'])
    airport_counts = data['airport'].value_counts().reset_index()
    airport_counts.columns = ['airport', 'count']
    least_popular_airport = airport_counts.loc[airport_counts['count'].idxmin()]

    ax = sns.barplot(x='airport', y='count', data=airport_counts, palette='viridis')
    ax.axhline(least_popular_airport['count'], color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Least popular: {least_popular_airport['count']:.2f}")
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('Airport')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the least popular airport for flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    heatmap_data = data.pivot_table(index='origin', columns='destination', values='count', aggfunc='sum')
    ax = sns.heatmap(heatmap_data, cmap='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flights between different origin and destination airports?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
